# ALPINE LINUX BASE IMAGE EXCEPTIONS
# ===========================================

# CVE-2023-4911 - glibc buffer overflow in ld.so (Alpine musl-libc not affected)
# Status: FALSE POSITIVE - Alpine uses musl-libc, not glibc
# Risk: Low - Does not affect Alpine Linux
# Justification: Trivy sometimes misidentifies musl-libc as vulnerable glibc
CVE-2023-4911

# CVE-2023-38545 - curl SOCKS5 heap buffer overflow
# Status: ACCEPTED RISK - Only affects curl with SOCKS5 proxy support
# Risk: Low - Application does not use SOCKS5 proxies
# Justification: Backend uses HTTP/HTTPS only, no SOCKS5 proxy functionality
CVE-2023-38545

# CVE-2023-38546 - curl SOCKS5 heap buffer overflow (follow-up)
# Status: ACCEPTED RISK - Same as CVE-2023-38545
# Risk: Low - No SOCKS5 proxy usage in application
# Justification: HTTP-only application, no proxy dependencies
CVE-2023-38546

